The paper deals with the optimization of neural networks, which is a central topic in machine learning. The paper proposes a novel framework for designing loss functions that can handle a wide range of input distributions. This makes it relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural networks (cs.NE), and statistics (cs.STAT). Among these, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category as it directly deals with the optimization of neural networks.
